# 02 вЂ” Build Standards

## DATABASE DESIGN (The Heart)

### Every Table Must Have
```sql
id              UUID PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid()
organization_id UUID NOT NULL REFERENCES organizations(id)
created_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
updated_at      TIMESTAMPTZ NOT NULL DEFAULT now()
created_by      UUID REFERENCES users(id)
```

### Non-Negotiable Rules
```
вњ“ RLS policies defined at table creation вЂ” never added later
вњ“ Every tenant-bound table has organization_id + workspace_id
вњ“ No cross-tenant data access under any circumstance
вњ“ Every migration has a rollback script
вњ“ Soft-delete: use deleted_at TIMESTAMPTZ, not DELETE
вњ“ Audit trail for any table where data changes matter
вњ“ Inventory counts derived from append-only log вЂ” never mutable integer
```

### Inventory / Batch / Spec Pattern
```
batch           в†’ group of items received at one time
spec            в†’ product variants (size, grade, weight range)
inventory_item  в†’ individual unit or lot within a batch
inventory_log   в†’ append-only record of every stock movement (insert only, never update)
```

### Schema Checklist Before Finalizing
```
вњ“ Can this table grow 100x without structural changes?
вњ“ Does every write have an audit record?
вњ“ Are RLS policies defined?
вњ“ Is the rollback migration written?
вњ“ Are indexes on actually-queried columns?
```

