## CODE QUALITY STANDARDS

Required for every code output:
- TypeScript strict mode вЂ” avoid `any`, explain if used
- Full words, semantic names, no unexplained abbreviations
- Every async has try/catch вЂ” errors logged, never silently swallowed
- Validate schema before processing вЂ” reject malformed data early
- All credentials via environment variables only
- Parameterized queries or ORM вЂ” never raw SQL concatenation

